  "title": "BUSINESS PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>* Plan, direct, and manage shipbuilding engineering projects, aligning resources, schedules, and priorities to achieve project objectives.</p><p>* Lead overall engineering project management for assigned shipbuilding projects, ensuring delivery within approved budget and timeline.</p><p>* Coordinate and integrate design and construction activities across technical and engineering disciplines to ensure seamless project execution.</p><p>* Develop, monitor, and control detailed project schedules and budgets, implementing corrective actions where necessary.</p><p>* Lead and manage an integrated project engineering team comprising hull structural, outfitting, electrical, and marine engineers (basic and detail design).</p><p>* Perform and oversee engineering detail design, developing technical solutions to resolve engineering issues in compliance with contractual specifications and marine classification rules.</p><p>* Ensure effective engineering configuration management throughout the project lifecycle.</p><p>* Lead design reviews, coordination meetings, and integration efforts, ensuring engineering and production drawings comply with contract requirements and marine classification standards.</p><p>* Ensure full compliance with applicable maritime regulations, classification society rules, company policies, and quality standards.</p><p>* Identify, assess, and mitigate project risks proactively to minimize impact on cost, schedule, and quality.</p><p>* Foster effective communication and collaboration with internal stakeholders, suppliers, subcontractors, and clients.</p><p>* Drive continuous improvement initiatives to enhance shipbuilding processes, engineering efficiency, and quality of deliverables.</p><p>* Prepare and present accurate project progress reports, technical updates, and management briefings to senior management and clients.</p>",
